<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" box="[151,795,258,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,244,258,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Length.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity box="[323,409,258,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
(n=1); female: 
<quantity box="[583,718,258,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="3.2" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.5 mm</quantity>
(n=4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" box="[199,1364,294,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,294,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Morphology.</emphasis>
Crown longer than distance between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[840,907,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[225,1352,217,1254]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[203,1374,193,1275]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cortona concordica sp. n. A, male habitus, dorsal view; B, macropterous female habitus, dorsal view; C, brachypterous female habitus, dorsal view; D, male habitus, lateral view; E, macropterous female habitus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376446/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
A–C). Male anteclypeus tapered distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,330,355]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate long, lateral margin distinctly concave. Style with articulating arm short; preapical lobe rectangular; apophysis slender, strongly curved, apex acuminate with small preapical tooth (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1934,1956]" captionTargetBox="[210,1367,1408,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1398,1375,1913]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cortona concordica sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, valve, subgenital plates, styles, connective, and aedeagus, ventral view; C, E, connective and aedeagus, ventral view and lateral view, respectively; D, detail of apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376447/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
B). Connective shorter than aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[650,738,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1934,1956]" captionTargetBox="[210,1367,1408,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1398,1375,1913]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cortona concordica sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, valve, subgenital plates, styles, connective, and aedeagus, ventral view; C, E, connective and aedeagus, ventral view and lateral view, respectively; D, detail of apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376447/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
C, 10E). Aedeagus slender, tapered from base to strongly acuminate apex, curved dorsad with distal appendages vestigial (
<figureCitation box="[877,957,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1934,1956]" captionTargetBox="[210,1367,1408,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1398,1375,1913]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cortona concordica sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, valve, subgenital plates, styles, connective, and aedeagus, ventral view; C, E, connective and aedeagus, ventral view and lateral view, respectively; D, detail of apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376447/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
C–E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,474,499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Female abdomen.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with median lobe covering approximately two-thirds of posterior margin, trilobed, median lobe slightly narrower and more produced than lateral lobes, with dark pigment indistinct (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1279,1301]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,205,1232]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[188,1398,193,1258]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Females of Cortona: A – D, Cortona minuta: A, first valvula; B, detail of first valvula apex; C, second valvula; D, third valvula. E – I, abdominal sternite VII: E, C. minuta; F, C. catanachae; G, C. silvai; H, C. otamendiensis; I, C. concordica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376448/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
Fig. 
<date box="[151,179,547,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" value="2011-01">11</date>
</figureCitation>
I).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
